@startuml
title MCP Tic-Tac-Toe — Two Paths to the Same Tools

' ---------- look & feel ----------
skinparam backgroundColor #f8fafc
skinparam shadowing false
skinparam roundCorner 14
skinparam defaultFontName "Segoe UI"
skinparam defaultFontSize 14
skinparam BoxPadding 18

skinparam sequence {
  ArrowColor #1e3a8a
  ArrowThickness 1.6
  ArrowFontColor #0f172a
  LifeLineBorderColor #94a3b8
  LifeLineBackgroundColor #e2e8f0
  ParticipantBorderColor #1e3a8a
  ParticipantBackgroundColor #dbeafe
  ParticipantFontColor #0f172a
  ActorBorderColor #1e3a8a
  ActorBackgroundColor #dbeafe
  ActorFontColor #0f172a
  DividerBackgroundColor #1e3a8a
  DividerFontColor #f8fafc
  DividerBorderColor #1e3a8a
}

skinparam Note {
  BackgroundColor #fef3c7
  BorderColor #d97706
  FontColor #78350f
}

' ---------- participants ----------
actor "User" as user
participant "Browser\n:8082" as browser
participant "MCP Client\n(Spring Boot)" as client
participant "MCP Server\n(Spring Boot)" as server
participant "Microsoft\nFoundry" as foundry

== A • Clicking the board ==

user -> browser : click cell
browser -> client : POST /api/game/move\n{gameId, position}
client -> server : **makeMove**(gameId, pos, "X")
server --> client : updated board
client -> server : **aiMove**(gameId)
server -> foundry : "Pick the best move 0–8"
foundry --> server : chosen index
server --> client : board after O
client --> browser : {board, status}
browser --> user : board updates

== B • Typing in the chat panel ==

user -> browser : "your turn"
browser -> client : POST /api/agent/chat\n{message, **gameId**}

note right of client #fef3c7
  First chat turn for a new gameId in this
  conversation: the client calls the real
  **getBoardState** MCP tool and appends
  the result to chat memory as an
  AssistantMessage — no prompt injection,
  just another tool call surfaced through
  conversation history.
end note

client -> server : **getBoardState**(gameId)
server --> client : board state JSON
client -> client : ChatMemory.add(AssistantMessage)

client -> foundry : user message + tool catalog\n+ chat memory (now seeded)
foundry --> client : "call **makeMove** then **aiMove**"
client -> server : makeMove / aiMove\n(same MCP tools as path A)
server --> client : final board
client --> browser : {reply, board}
browser --> user : chat reply + board updates

@enduml
